dct_title_s: Kosmosdale quadrangle, Kentucky-Indiana : 15 minute series (topographic) [1959 reprint with vegetation]
dct_description_sm: Mapped by the Geological Survey and the Army Map Service , published for civil use by the Geological Survey. Filing title: Kosmodale, Ky.-Ind. Polyconic projection. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Contour interval 20 feet. Dashed lines represent 10-foot contours. Some copies show forest areas colored green. "Compiled in 1953 from 1:25000 scale maps of Lousiville West, Lanesville, Kosmosdale, and Valley Station 7.5 minute quadrangles, surveyed in 1950. Topography from aerial photographs by photogrammetric methods. Aerial photographs taken 1947 and 1949. Field check 1950." "This area also covered by 1:24000 scale maps of Louisville West, Lanesville, Kosmosdale, and Valley Station 7.5 minute quadrangles, surveyed 1955." "N3800--W8545/15."
dct_creator_sm: United States. Army. Corps of Engineers; Geological Survey (U.S.)
